FBIS4-13760 "drnes079_p_94002" FBIS-NES-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Government Forces Kill Golboddin Commander, 24 Men Government Forces Kill Golboddin Commander, 24 Men LD2304191394 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304191394 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Pashto BFN [Text] Woreshmin, a commander attached to Golboddin, together with his 24 men were killed in the vicinity of Bala Hesar during the recent operation carried out by Karmal-Golboddin-Dostam militia. The BIA military correspondent reports that during a counterattack, the military forces of the Islamic State of Afghanistan forced the Karmal-Golboddin-Dostam militia to retreat and imposed heavy losses on the aggressors. The report adds that Woreshmin was a general attached to Toran Amanollah. He had intended to appoint Woreshmin as chief of staff of his forces.
